     <h2><b>Savour The Best Biryani In Bangalore At These Iconic Joints :-</b></h2>
     <br>
     
     <div class="container">
     
     <h3>1. Meghna Foods</h3>
     
     <img alt="" src="https://vaya.in/recipes/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Ambur-Chicken-Biriyani.jpg" height="200" width="400">
     <br>
     <p>Popularly known among Bangaloreans for its scrumptious Andhra-style chicken biryani, Meghana biryani (undoubtedly) shelters the most flavourful biryani in the city. With branches all across Bangalore (to cater to the cravings of oodles of biryani devotees) this iconic joint serves plenty of delish varieties of this toothsome dish. All the meat-lovers can relish their delicious mutton biryani, while the vegetarians in the house can indulge in their appetising paneer variant.
Where: Meghana Foods, Koramangala
When: 11:45 pm to 4 pm and 7 pm to 11 pm
Price: Rs. 230 for two
Contact: 080 41463738</p>

<h3>2. Savoury Sea Shell
</h3>
     
     <img alt="" src="https://tbsnews.net/sites/default/files/styles/big_2/public/images/2021/03/19/biriyani.jpg?itok=vhPO3pu2&timestamp=1616129015" height="200" width="400">
     <br>
     <p>Home to the juiciest shawarmas in the city, Savoury Sea Shell is a Arabian speciality restaurant which serves flavour-rich I. A small, hidden section in their relatively elaborate menu features a range of scrumptious biryani variants to choose from, out of which the Mutton Raan Biryani steals the show. Their standard chicken and mutton biryani variants too are aromatic and mouth-watering, making this a great eatery to check out.
Where: Savoury Restaurant, Frazer Town
When: 8 am to 1 am
Price: Rs. 250 for two
Contact: 080 49336333</p>

<h3>3. Samarkand

</h3>
     
     <img alt="" src="http://www.bakespace.com/images/large/f468b5f5247496b4f854e203bd46a7cd.jpeg" height="200" width="400">
     <br>
     <p>If you are struck by a craving for authentic Nawaabi Khaana, then you should unquestionably stop by at the Samarkand Restaurant on Infantry road, to indulge in their rich Nawaabi menu! All biryani junkies (like ourselves) CAN NOT afford to miss their flavour-laden Handi Ghosht Biryani, which is a mouth-watering amalgamation of juicy meat, fragrant spices and flavourful rice. Besides the delectable biryani, do try their succulent kebabs and exceptionally good seafood!! You will be left asking for more. 
Where: Samarkand, Shivaji Nagar
When:12 pm to 3:30 pm, 7 pm to 11 pm
Price: Rs.1600 for two
Contact: 080 41113366</p>


 

